PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions About Ethereum Transaction Analysis
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Ethereum transaction analysis involves monitoring and inspecting new transactions on the Ethereum blockchain to gain insights into activity, trends, and potential security issues or fraudulent behavior.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_2: How does the app analyze transactions?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: The app connects to Ethereum nodes to stream new transaction data in real-time. It then parses and processes this data, applying heuristics and rules to detect patterns of interest.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_3: What kind of insights can be gained?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: Some insights include identifying high-value transactions, tracking activity of specific wallets or smart contracts, detecting potential money laundering or theft, and monitoring decentralized applications.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Is the app suitable for security auditing?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: While the app can surface potential security risks, it is primarily an analysis tool. For comprehensive smart contract auditing, you should engage certified blockchain security auditors.
CTA_BODY: Gain valuable insights into the latest activities on the Ethereum blockchain with our powerful transaction analysis tool. Monitor new transactions as they occur and dive deep into transaction details, wallet addresses, and blockchain data.

FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Everything you need to know about analyzing new Ethereum transactions
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: This app allows you to analyze and monitor new transactions occurring on the Ethereum blockchain in real-time. It provides insights into transaction details, wallet activity, and overall network metrics.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: The app connects to Ethereum nodes and listens for new blocks being added to the blockchain. When a new block is detected, it parses the transactions and extracts relevant data for analysis.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: What kind of data can I see?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: You can view details like the sender and receiver addresses, transaction value, gas fees, transaction status, and timestamps. The app also calculates analytics like transaction volume, active wallets, and token transfers.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Yes, the basic version of the app is completely free to use. We offer premium plans with additional features and higher data limits for power users and enterprises.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Simply sign up on our website and download the app. The onboarding process will guide you through connecting to Ethereum nodes and customizing your transaction monitoring preferences.
